# nektos/act default flags. Loaded automatically when `act` is invoked from
# this repository's root. Real GitHub Actions runners ignore this file, so
# settings here only affect local act runs.
#
# Override per-invocation by passing the same flag with a different value on
# the command line.

# Pin runner image to a known-good catthehacker variant for reproducibility.
#
# `full-22.04` (~18 GB) ships the same tool set as github-hosted ubuntu-22.04
# runners, including a recent docker CLI. The slimmer `act-latest` image
# (~2 GB) ships an older docker CLI that defaults to API version 1.32, which
# OrbStack and Docker Engine 24+ reject when Testcontainers reaches the
# host daemon through the bind-mounted socket ("client version 1.32 is too
# old. Minimum supported API version is 1.40"). The full image avoids that
# trip wire and matches the daemon api floor of github-hosted runners.
# (unverified - confirm by running the backend job under act after first
# pull; cold pull is large.)
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:full-22.04

# Force amd64 so behavior matches GitHub-hosted ubuntu-latest. On Apple
# Silicon hosts this runs through Rosetta in Docker Desktop / OrbStack /
# Colima.
--container-architecture linux/amd64

# Emulated artifact server for actions/upload-artifact and download-artifact.
# Without this flag, upload steps fail with
#   ::error::Unable to get the ACTIONS_RUNTIME_TOKEN env variable
# Path is on the host filesystem; act mounts it into the runner container.
--artifact-server-path /tmp/act-artifacts

# Local-only credentials and config files. All three paths are gitignored
# (.github/env.local, .github/secrets.local, .github/vars.local). Populate
# them yourself; templates live next to them as *.example if added later.
--env-file .github/env.local
--secret-file .github/secrets.local
--var-file .github/vars.local

# Container options applied to the runner container itself.
#   --group-add=0
#       Adds the root group so the bind-mounted /var/run/docker.sock is
#       readable from inside the runner. Required for docker-cli, compose,
#       and Testcontainers calls that touch the daemon.
#
# Limitation: act's `--container-options` is a single-string flag, and
# `.actrc` lines are split on whitespace before parsing. That means you
# cannot pack multiple docker options into this one line, and adding
# additional `--container-options=` lines does not stack (last one wins).
# Pass extra docker options via a shell-quoted CLI invocation when needed,
# e.g. on a plain Linux Docker Engine daemon (no Docker Desktop / OrbStack)
# where `host.docker.internal` is not auto-provided:
#
#     act --container-options "--group-add=0 \
#         --add-host=host.docker.internal:host-gateway" -W ...
#
# On macOS with Docker Desktop or OrbStack the alias is injected into every
# container's /etc/hosts natively, so the bare `--group-add=0` below is
# enough for ci.yml's BACKEND_HOST and TESTCONTAINERS_HOST_OVERRIDE to
# resolve.
--container-options=--group-add=0
